## Constraints

- Use the `agent-memory` skill to log your work and reasoning. Refer back to those logs when restoring context or as needed.
- Update `ARCHITECTURE.md` files when architecture or design decisions change
- Follow the architecture and design defined in `ARCHITECTURE.md` files
- Maintain an `ARCHITECTURE.md` in every application and shared package directory, scoped to that directory. Add one to any other significant subdirectory when it owns distinct responsibilities, boundaries, data flows, or design decisions.
- Before adding a directory for executable code or scripts, assess whether it belongs in the shared uv/pnpm workspace. Prefer an application in `apps/`, a reusable package in `packages/`, or a skill-owned script under `.agents/skills/` over a new root-level `scripts/` directory.
- Reserve `repos/` for child Git submodules; do not add ordinary source files there.
- Automate repetitive, deterministic tasks with scripts
- Prefer Python for general scripting and automation
- Consider creating an Agent Skill for reusable qualitative workflows that are not easy to script but can be reliably performed by an agent
- Continuously maintain repository-level Agent Skills using the SkillOpt-informed review principles defined by the `agent-skill-authoring` skill
- Report to the user in Japanese

